  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Valor Venture Fund II, LP</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting innovation, creating markets and providing access to capital:  Startups in emerging markets currently lack access to patient equity capital, global know-how and operational support that professional fund managers offer. Early stage companies need cash infusions in relatively quick successions as they achieve scale. Without adequate funding, they would not be able to sustain operations and be forced to abandon their pursuit of developing disruptive businesses. Thus, there is a significant role for governments and developmental finance institutions to play in helping to support and sustain entrepreneurship and innovation in underserved markets. Access to equity is difficult for asset light businesses such as technology firms. IFC&apos;s commitment would provide the necessary patient capital to support and grow such innovative businesses.    Global expansion of local businesses:  The Fund will support an innovation ecosystem around its investees to maximize success potential and foster skills development and international best practice. The project is expected to reach 25 early stage companies and improve operations with proper guidance.    Governance, and operational improvements:  IFC will offer guidance and ensure that local businesses implement best practices in various fields.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed is an equity investment of up to $7M in Valor Venture Fund II, (Fund II), a Cayman domiciled venture capital (VC) fund focused on investing in early-stage technology companies in Brazil.</narrative>
  </description>
